<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent: -.5in; margin: 0in 0in .0001pt .5in;"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span lang="EN-GB">&nbsp;</span></strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent: -.5in; margin: 0in 0in .0001pt .5in;"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span lang="EN-GB">11.<span style="mso-tab-count: 1;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Complaints</span></strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt; text-align: justify;"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span lang="EN-GB">&nbsp;</span></strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; margin: 0in 0in .0001pt .5in;"><span lang="EN-GB" style="  ">If you are of the belief that your privacy rights have been breached, you should contact our HIPAA Privacy Officer at [ support@clinicalmatch.com ]. You also have a right to file a complaint with the Secretary of the U. S. Department of Health and Human Services, by mail to 200 Independence Avenue, Washington DC, 20201 or by calling 1-877-696-6775 or visiting </span><span lang="EN-GB"><a href="http://www.hhs.gov/ocr/privacy/hipaa/complaints"><span style="   color: #0563c1;">www.hhs.gov/ocr/privacy/hipaa/complaints</span></a></span><span lang="EN-GB" style="  ">. You will not be penalized in any way if you do file a complaint against </span><span lang="EN-GB">ClinicalMatch.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: .0001pt; text-align: center;" align="center"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span lang="EN-GB">&nbsp;</span></strong></p>
